Chaotic scenes played out once again at the Pan African Parliament. This as leadership elections were due to get underway this afternoon. eNCA's Khayelihle Khumalo is following today's proceedings and spoke to EFF leader Julius Malema. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - The Pan African Parliament's leadership rotation is something that EFF leader and PAP MP Julius Malema is willing to die for. The house was adjourned after fighting erupted for the second-day on Tuesday. WATCH: Fight over Pan-African Parliament leadership rotation system Speaking to eNCA, Malema says they can't shy away from the issue anymore. A number of MP's mostly from Francophone countries are opposing the PAP rotation.  #PanAfricanParliament Yet another heated session. pic.twitter.com/MrZhTsJoGA